            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pinion nut, washer and end yoke. Apply a light coat of lubricant to the lip of
                    the seal and assemble Into housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble end yoke, washer, and new pinion nut. Tighten to:</para>
                <para>700 to 900 ft-lbs. (949 to 1220 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Recheck torque to rotate.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate carrier to vertical position with yoke down. Install pinion roller bearing
                    retainer, using soft hammer if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four retainer bolts. Tighten bolts to:</para>
                <para>14CDA, 14130 - 70 to 80 ft-lbs. (95 to 108 N&#8226;m).</para>
                <para>14131, 14132, 14133, 14CDB - 110 to 125 ft-lbs. (149 to 169 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </step1>
